<body>
    <h1>API Documentation</h1>
    <div class="endpoint">
      <h2>About API</h2>
      <p><b>qrcodeGen</b> is a qrcode generating API, request can be sent via CURL, Postman or any other API client, and also example illustrated below is in CURL</p>
    </div>
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h2>POST /api/v1/qrcode/gen</h2>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong> Generates a qrcode image with the text provided in request body.</p>
        <div class="request">
            <h3>Request</h3>
            <p class="code">POST /api/v1/qrcode/gen\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  "text": "www.google.com"\n}</p>
        </div>
        <div class="response">
            <h3>Response</h3>
            <p class="code">HTTP/1.1 201 Created\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n[{"message":"qrcode generated,"imgname":"qrcode_yw6h.png"}]</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h2>GET /api/v1/qrcode/image/{imagename}</h2>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong> Displays the specified qrcode image on the webpage.</p>
        <div class="request">
            <h3>Request</h3>
            <p class="code">GET /api/v1/qrcode/image/qrcode_yw6h.png</p>
        </div>
        <div class="response">
            <h3>Response</h3>
            <p class="code">HTTP/1.1 201 Created\nContent-Type: img/png</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr>
